{"section": "3.13.1: Using the well-ordering principle.", "qid": 3, "instructions": "<div class=\"activity-instructions\">\n <p>\n  The well-ordering principle can be used to prove any fact which can be proven by standard or strong induction.\n </p>\n <p>\n  Consider again the problem of purchasing cans of juice. Suppose that juice is sold in 2-packs or 5-packs. Let Q(n) be the statement that it is possible to buy n cans of juice by combining 2-packs and 5-packs. We can use the principle of well-ordering to show that for\n  <span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n   n \u2265 4,\n  </span>\n  Q(n) is true.\n </p>\n</div>\n", "question": "<div class=\"question\">\n <div class=\"setup flex-row\">\n  <div class=\"label\">\n   4)\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"text\">\n   What is the contradiction that results if m \u2265 6?\n  </div>\n </div>\n <fieldset>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember123\" style=\"\">\n   <input aria-label=\"It is possible to buy m - 2 cans. m cans can be purchased by buying m - 2 cans and adding a 2-pack.\" name=\"14\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember122&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"\">\n    It is possible to buy\n    <span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n     m - 2\n    </span>\n    cans. m cans can be purchased by buying\n    <span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n     m - 2\n    </span>\n    cans and adding a 2-pack.\n   </label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember125\">\n   <input aria-label=\"Q(6) is true because it is possible to buy 6 cans by purchasing three 2-packs.\" name=\"14\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember124&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n    Q(6) is true because it is possible to buy 6 cans by purchasing three 2-packs.\n   </label>\n  </div>\n </fieldset>\n</div>\n", "choices": ["<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember123\">\n <input aria-label=\"It is possible to buy m - 2 cans. m cans can be purchased by buying m - 2 cans and adding a 2-pack.\" name=\"14\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember122&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  It is possible to buy\n  <span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n   m - 2\n  </span>\n  cans. m cans can be purchased by buying\n  <span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n   m - 2\n  </span>\n  cans and adding a 2-pack.\n </label>\n</div>\n", "<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember125\">\n <input aria-label=\"Q(6) is true because it is possible to buy 6 cans by purchasing three 2-packs.\" name=\"14\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember124&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  Q(6) is true because it is possible to buy 6 cans by purchasing three 2-packs.\n </label>\n</div>\n"], "answer": "It is possible to buy m - 2 cans. m cans can be purchased by buying m - 2 cans and adding a 2-pack.", "explanation": "<div aria-atomic=\"true\" class=\"explanation has-explanation correct\" role=\"alert\">\n <p class=\"message\">\n  Correct\n </p>\n Since m \u2265 6, m - 2 is  in the range from 4 to m-1, so Q(m - 2) is true and it is possible to buy m - 2 cans. By adding a 2-pack, it is possible to buy m cans and Q(m) is true.\n</div>\n"}